x4freetext: kinematics using 87-Kr beam on deuterated polyethylene
target at the Argonne Tandem-Linac Accelerator
Out-going light ions were analyzed using the
a superconducting solenoidal magnet with its axis
along the beam direction. It is 2.35 m in length
with a bore of 0.9 m and a central field set at 2 T.
Protons were detected using an array of 24
position-sensitive Si detectors, arranged in rings
of four around the axis in a box configuration.
The silicon detectors measure the ion energy,
the position along the axis, and the time of flight
relative to the radio frequency of the ATLAS
